author: Messenger Post sports@messengerpostmedia.com
title: HS roundup: Honeoye outlasts H-AC in girls volleyball
text: Posted Oct. 19, 2015 at 11:10 PM Canandaigua, N.Y. It came down to five games and what better way to set the tone in the deciding game than to go on an 11-point service run? That’s what Hailey Cornish did for the Honeoye girls volleyball team, which defeated Harley-Allendale Columbia on Monday night by scores of 25-23, 20-25, 25-21, 15-25 and 25-9. The win gives the Bulldogs a 7-2 record in the Finger Lakes West and a 13-2 overall mark. H-AC falls to 4-5, 8-7. Cornish finished with 10 aces, 35 assists and 24 digs, while Lydia Barnard had 26 kills and 22 digs. Bailey Lis had six kills and five blocks, and Margaret Slocum and Kenzie Helling each had 13 digs. Rebecca Orbach led H-AC with 21 kills and 15 digs while Caroline Mealey added 11 kills and 22 digs. South Seneca 26-25-25, Bloomfield 24-18-22 Carissa Beatty had 10 digs and two aces while Sierra Leitten had 4 aces, 2 kills and 11 assists for the Bombers (2-6, 6-8). Bailey Minges led South Seneca (8-1, 13-3) with 18 assists, 7 kills, 2 aces and 7 digs while Laura Wyckoff had 9 kills, 7 assists, 4 aces and 7 digs. Girls tennis Mynderse 5, Waterloo 0 Samantha Pundt, Rachel Sullivan and Meredith Perine all scored singles points for Mynderse (16-2) in a makeup match from Sept. 29. Waterloo is 0-11 and Mynderse finishes with an 8-2 league record to share the Finger Lakes West title with Naples. Saturday Girls tennis Section V championships The top-seeded Victor doubles team of Emily Stanley and Sarah Marro defeated No. 2 seed Xilin Zhou and Catherine Gamble of Webster Schroeder, 6-2, 6-4, to win the Class AA individual title at the Mendon Racquet and Pool Club. In Class B, the Palmyra-Macedon doubles team of Marietta Koeberle and Anna O'Donnell lost to Batavia’s Stephanie Hoy and Sophia Stuart, 4-6, 6-1, 6-4. In the singles playbacks, Pal-Mac’s Erin Graham defeated Natasha Neckles of Greece Odyssey, 6-1, 6-3 and Pal-Mac’s Cara Graham defeated Melissa Mountain of Batavia, 6-1, 6-4. In the Class CC playbacks, Molly Cole of Wellsville defeated Teresa Craugh of Marcus Whitman, 6-4, 7-5. In Class, top seed Lexi Sanford of Prattsburgh defeated No. 2 Hannah Delgatto of Naples, 6-1, 6-2, in the singles final. The Naples doubles team of Sam Spofford and Avril King dropped a 3-6, 6-4, 7-6 (2) decision to Micayah Ambriz and Catie Moore Prattsburgh. By Messenger Post
